    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Class of circular or radiating boulder outlines built by ancient North American Indian peoples of the Great Plains. These enigmatic archaeological features are believed to have some religious, astronomical, territorial, or calendrical significance.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
